The 2020 edition of the Swannies Racing Series is finally here and quad and two-wheel biking enthusiasts are expected to converge in numbers for the adrenaline creating event at Ysterberg on Saturday.
The endurance ride promises to test bikers’ skills and most important their strength during the race.
Trophies are up for grabs to all podium winners in various categories of quad and two-wheel bikes.
Registration fees are R450 per bike for those participating in the four laps of 35 km and R250 for the kiddies’ race consisting of an 8 km lap to be ridden for two hours.
Visitors and spectators will have to pay R20 per vehicle to be able to join in the challenging event. Registration can be done on the race day prior to the start which is scheduled for 10:00.
Participants can travel on the R101 until they find the Geyser turn-off and follow the signs to the venue. Alternatively make use of the GPS location 24°02’07.6”S 29°14’06.9”E
Food and drinks will be on sale.
For more information contact Peet or Swannie Swanepoel on 083 469 0138 or 071 859 6924 respectively.
